WorkItem.Description:
Hi guys,

I am pretty new to PHP and PHPExcel, and I am wondering how I can fill some data to a xls file and then save it as a pdf? I've been able to fill in data to xls and save it as xls.. but I would like to save it as a pdf.

I've downloaded domPDF but I'm not sure on how to use it..

This is my code so far (loadSummary.php):

```
    include 'PHPExcel.php';
    include 'PHPExcel/Writer/PDF.php';

   $rendererName = PHPExcel_Settings::PDF_RENDERER_DOMPDF;
    $rendererLibraryPath = dirname(__FILE__). '\dompdf';
    PHPExcel_Settings::setPdfRenderer($rendererName, $rendererLibraryPath);
    if (!PHPExcel_Settings::setPdfRenderer($rendererName, $rendererLibraryPath)) {
        die('Please set the $rendererName and $rendererLibraryPath values as appropriate for your directory structure');
    }

    $template = '../templates/template.xls';
    $objPHPExcel = PHPExcel_IOFactory::load($template);
    $today = date('dmyHi');
    $newFilename = 'test_' . $today . '.pdf';

    $objWorksheet = $objPHPExcel->getSheet(0);
    $objPHPExcel->setActiveSheetIndex(0);

    /*
    Fill in data here...
    */
    $objWriter = PHPExcel_IOFactory::createWriter($objPHPExcel, 'PDF'); 
    $objWriter->save("../".$newFilename);
```

Here is my folder structure:

